The paper deals with the problem of image detection in agriculture, specifically in corn fields. This falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) category. The paper also proposes a model based on convolutional neural networks (CNN), which is a popular topic in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions the use of ResNet, which is a deep learning architecture commonly used in image recognition (cs.IR). Finally, the paper discusses the evaluation of the proposed method, which involves training and testing the model, a process that is often associated with neural networks (cs.NE).
